data.description: Nestled at the base of the majestic Ben Lomond, this exquisite residence is a crowning jewel among a neighborhood of opulent estates. Enveloped by a landscape of multi-million dollar homes, this stunning property radiates an unparalleled level of luxury and grandeur.  Step into this expansive home, boasting 6 bedrooms and 5 baths, meticulously designed and fully finished to absolute perfection. No detail has been spared in crafting this abode, where every facet has been meticulously thought out to create a complete masterpiece of modern living.  A sanctuary for relaxation and entertainment, the outdoor space is a true oasis. Gather with loved ones around the expansive fire pit, accompanied by a serene cascading waterfall. Sports enthusiasts can indulge in the dedicated sports court, perfect for honing skills in games like pickleball.  The grandeur of this residence extends indoors, where an XL deck connected to the family room and primary suite provides sweeping views of the entire valley. From this vantage point, revel in the breathtaking scenery-the city skyline, the Great Salt Lake, and the stunning play of seasonal hues painting the mountains.  Each room within this home is a picture-perfect frame showcasing one of the most mesmerizing panoramas in the world. The main floor hosts a palatial primary suite with a recently customized walk-in closet that caters to every need. The primary bath, reminiscent of a Zen-like retreat, features a custom shower with double shower heads and a private mountain view, a true testament to the luxury embedded in every corner.  The upper level unveils a second primary suite with its own walk-in closet and full bath. Three loft areas offer versatility-a crafting haven equipped with a sink and a balcony to draw inspiration from the mountain views, an entertainment zone housing a video arcade and an air hockey table, and the pinnacle of leisure.  The basement embraces four XL bedrooms, complemented by a Jack and Jill bath and a stand-alone full bath. A family room, kitchenette, and a second laundry area enrich the lower-level living space. Step out onto a private covered patio, an idyllic spot for unwinding in the hot tub while witnessing nature's theatrics as storms roll in.  Practicality meets convenience with an RV pad and an extra deep 3rd car garage, catering to storage needs for all your recreational vehicles and toys. Did I mention this home has paid for solar panels? Enjoy minimal electric bills and have the freedom of power. There are enough panels to run a future swimming pool too.    This residence, a true embodiment of beauty, must be seen to be believed.  Details and Square footage figures are provided as a courtesy estimate only and were obtained from the County record.  The buyer is advised to obtain an independent measurement.
